[[File:Ulysses, 1922.djvu|thumb|600px|center|page=24]]
<br>
==Annotations==
'''''Zut ! Nom de Dieu !'''''{{spaces|5}}(''French'') ''Go to hell! Goddamn!''<ref>Gifford (1988) 26.</ref> ''Zut'' is a coarse exclamation signifying refusal or (as here) dismissal.<ref>[http://books.google.ie/books?id=EOxRfo8_RE4C Alfred Delvau, ''Dictionnaire de la Langue Verte''.]</ref> ''[[wikt:nom de Dieu|Nom de Dieu]]'' (literally, ''name of God'') is a blasphemous oath signifying shock or indignation.

