[[File:Ulysses, 1922.djvu|thumb|600px|center|page=34]]
<br>
==Annotations==
'''''Per vias rectas'''''{{spaces|5}}(''Latin'') ''By straight roads;'' ''By straight paths.'' This is the Blackwood family motto.<ref>[http://www.houseofnames.com/blackwood-family-crest House of Names.]<br>{{cite book |last1 = Gifford |first1 = Don |last2 = Seidman |first2 = Robert J. |title = Ulysses Annotated |publisher = University of California Press |year = 1988 |page =37}}</ref> It is also the school motto of [[w:Belvedere College|Belvedere College]] in Dublin, which Joyce attended from 1893 until 1898.<ref>{{cite book |last1 = Ellmann|first1 = Richard |title = James Joyce |publisher = Oxford University Press |year = 1982 |pages = 35-56}}</ref>


