[[File:Ulysses, 1922.djvu|thumb|600px|center|page=106]]
<br>
==Annotations==
'''''Habeat corpus'''''{{spaces|5}}(''Latin'') ''Let him have the body.'' Bloom has adapted the legal term ''[[w:Habeas corpus|Habeas corpus]]'' (''May you have the body''), a writ requiring a prisoner to appear in person before a judge so that the judge may determine whether or not he has been lawfully detained .

