</includeonly>

[[File:Ulysses, 1922.djvu|thumb|600px|center|page=165]]
<br>
==Annotations==
'''''table d'hôte'' she called it'''{{spaces|5}}(''French'') ''Table d'hôte'' is a fixed menu in a hotel, offering a fixed meal at a set price. The ''she'' Bloom refers to may be ''[[Annotations_to_James_Joyce's_Ulysses/Cyclops/293|Mrs O'Dowd that kept the hotel]]''.


