==Annotations==
'''''Pfuiteufel !'''''{{spaces|5}}(''German'') ''Pfui'' is the German for ''[[wikt:fie|fie!]]'' and ''Teufel'' means ''Devil''. Together, ''Pfui Teufel!'' means ''Disgusting! Yuck! Ugh! [[wikt:ew|Ew!]]''<ref>Gifford (1988) 198.</ref> I have not found a German instance in which the two words are yoked together as here.<ref>[http://www.dict.cc/?s=Pfui%20Teufel ''Pfui Teufel''.]</ref>


