==Annotations==
'''''idée fixe'''''{{spaces|5}}(''French'') obsession; fixed idea.<ref>Gifford (1988) 281.</ref> This French term was first coined by the composer [[w:Hector Berlioz|Hector Berlioz]] to describe a recurring musical motif in his ''Symphonie fantastique'' that represents the artist's obsessive love for his beloved. In 1885 it was established as a quasi-technical term in psychiatry to describe a form of neurotic obsession known today as [[w:Monomania|monomania]].

