==Annotations==
'''''da capo'''''{{spaces|5}}(''Italian'') ''from the beginning''.<ref>Gifford (1988) 310.</ref> This [[w:Glossary of musical terminology|musical term]] directs the performer to repeat a passage from the beginning. Bloom seems to be making the point that every trade has its own musical signature, which is then simply repeated ad nauseam.

