'''South Africa''' is a large country in southern Africa.  It is bordered by [[../Namibia|Namibia]], [[../Botswana|Botswana]], [[../Zimbabwe|Zimbabwe]], [[../Mozambique|Mozambique]], [[../Swaziland|Swaziland]].  [[../Lesotho|Lesotho]] is an enclave (''completely surrounded by South Africa'') within South Africa.  Interestingly, South Africa has '''3 capital cities:''' Pretoria (executive capital), Bloemfontein (judicial capital), Cape Town (legislative capital).  Johannesburg is the country's biggest city.

==Geography==

==History==

==Economy==

==People==
There are '''11 official languages''' in South Africa: [[Wikijunior:Languages/Afrikaans|Afrikaans]], [[Wikijunior:Languages/English|English]], Southern Ndebele, Northern Sotho, Southern Sotho, Swazi, Tsonga, Tswana, Venda, [[Wikijunior:Languages/Xhosa|Xhosa]] and Zulu.  Afrikaans, Zulu and Xhosa are the most widely-spoken first languages although the majority of people know English as a second language.

