==Annotations==
'''''foetus in foetu'''''{{spaces|5}}(''Latin'') ''foetus in a foetus'', a [[w:Fetus in fetu|medical term]] describing a foetus growing inside the body of another foetus, either from an unsuccessful twin pregnancy, or as a tumor-like growth.<ref>Gifford (1988) 430 translates the term as ''fetus at birth'', which is incorrect.</ref>

