{{BookCat}}

[[File:Ulysses, 1922.djvu|thumb|600px|center|page=397]]
<br>
==Annotations==
'''''Lacus Mortis'''''{{spaces|5}}(''Latin'') ''Lake of Death''.<ref>Gifford (1988) 433.</ref> Hence, the [[w:Dead Sea|Dead Sea]]. The usual Latin name is ''[[w:la:Mare Mortuum|Mare Mortuum]]''. The basaltic plain on the Moon known as the ''[[w:Lacus Mortis|Lacus Mortis]]'' was only named in 1935, thirteen years after the publication of ''Ulysses''. See also [[Annotations_to_James_Joyce's_Ulysses/Calypso/059|059.01-09]] and '''394.15'''.


