==Annotations==
'''Kithogue'''{{spaces|5}}(''Hiberno-English'') ''Lefty!'' A ''kithogue'' is a left-handed person. Both the Hiberno-English term and the Irish word (''ciotóg'') from which it is derived carry connotations of awkwardness.

